The sidewalks are really bad and falling apart, and most of the buildings on it look shabby. There are a lot of trees on this street, but that is probably to hide what the buildings look like. Most of the crime in my area has happened at an apartment complex on that street, but then again, I can’t blame just them. There are apartments across the street from me that also have a lot of crime and a rather transient population. But I think I like where I live. I can afford it, and there’s plenty of useful amenities nearby. I especially like how the university is within walking distance and there are two bus stops so that I can get to the store and downtown with ease.
My neighborhood is made up of duplex's on a cul-de-sac. They are intermittently placed and spaced so that they look like individual houses. The only difference is each is painted yellow with white porches and green metal roofs. Almost everyone, but not all, are friends with each other. We stand at the end of a not pre-decided driveway some evenings and chit chat while the small children of the neighborhood play with their toys, sidewalk chalk or fly their kites. It is very refreshing in this modern all to mechanical/computer filled world. It is rather like stepping back in time. We are surrounded by fields and trees enhanced by blue skies and white billowing clouds. The only downfall? This season, we are experiencing tornado warnings and for the first time, last night we actually heard actual tornado sirens so we had to head towards shelter. Sure enough, you would have found me in my bathtub clutching my littlest dog along with my purse and a few pillows. My big dog wanted nothing to do with the bathroom and remained in the livingroom, nervous and barking, nervous about the odd circumstances. The neighborhood was quiet except for the sound of large hail which fell all bout the ground. After the storm the road literally was steaming from the change of temperature. We went from 92 to 75 in a matter of minutes. The hail immediately melted when it hit the hot pavement. As I looked up towards the clearing skies, the sun came out and it started to rain. A double rainbow apparated. I ran into the house and grabbed my camera. Quickly snapped pictures to share with my Facebook friends and family. They were in awe, as was I. The streets remained quiet for another hour, before some people finally came home from wherever they were when the thunderstorm hit. Then it was business as usual, mom’s and children outside as dinner cooked. Such a friendly neighborhood for this gal who has recently moved form NH to NC. I adore the southern accent that people speak with. I have a two bedroom and two bath apartment, as does everyone. Though all the houses look the same on the outside, not all of the apartments are the same on the inside. Some are actually quite tiny. It doesn’t make sense to me. I love to walk along the biggest field behind where I live and mosey down to the pond that is not made for swimming. I have seen deer and in the morning you can hear the giant bullfrog singing his song. It is a fantastic place to live just forty minutes outside the city of Charlotte. Each morning is welcomed by the sound of roosters crowing from the surrounding farms. It is rather like living in a small community village of it’s own. We even have a donkey at a nearby farm that you can hear braying in the evening to let us know he is there. I was lucky to find this gem of a neighborhood.
I moved to this neighborhood just when I was about to start eighth grade. It was hard for me to make friends at first, but I ended up getting close to someone who lives two houses down from me and another guy that lives on my street. Neither of them lives there anymore but the memories are still there. The same people who lived here when I first moved here are still here for the most part. My neighborhood is pretty similar to your average American suburban neighborhood. The neighborhood has a lot of two-story houses in it. Every weekend or just whenever it is warm outside I hear the kids playing outside. The neighborhood is quiet most days of the week. I have never had a problem with any of the people in the neighborhood. You are left alone in this neighborhood unless you need help. I have ordered multiple packages online and have never gotten a package snatched off of my porch. I feel like I can trust my neighbors. There is a park a minute or two away from my house. I have a lot of memories there. I have played basketball, football, and baseball there with the other guys in the neighborhood before. I also ended up with one of my worst memories there when I got elbowed in the nose playing football, but the good memories outweigh the bad. Nowadays, whenever I go to that park it is to spend time with my cousin's kids. They are much younger than me and still like playing on swings and slides and all of that type of stuff. Just the thought of going to the park makes them excited. The park makes me very nostalgic for a number of different reasons now. The neighborhood is very diverse. You will find all kinds of food nearby. In just a one mile radius, you would be able to find Chinese, Indian, Mexican, and Italian restaurants. However, nowadays, a lot of people just use apps just as GrubHub and DoorDash to get their food delivered to them. The most popular food places are the fast food shops but you can get those near pretty much any suburban neighborhood. There are also plenty of pizza places. The stores here contain everything you would ever need. There are multiple dry cleaners nearby. There is a Walgreens and a CVS on the same street as well as a Jewel-Osco grocery store, which is popular in the Midwest. Some of the stores are even diverse as there is an Indian-owned store if you are ever in the mood to make some homemade Indian food or to buy some ready-made Indian food. Overall, I am a fan of my neighborhood. Reading on social media and seeing on the news some of the horror stories other people have to go through with their neighbors makes me grateful for mine.
My neighborhood is a quaint little town. It doesn't stand out from any other in South Carolina, but it's got a significant impact on the agriculture sector. Johnston is known as the Peach Capital of the World, something that the town proudly boasts about on the welcoming sign. It's primarily composed of farmland dominated by either peach trees or cattle. Houses that aren't located within the main part of town are widely spaced apart; most are two stories with either metal roofs to help combat the blazing summer heat or gray shingles. More often than not these houses aren't located near the road, but are further back allowing for the front fields to be used for animals/crops. Within the main part of town, there's a single stop light that hangs at a four way. Here is where the only stores in the entire town are located. There are three places in which you can get "fast food': Hong Kong, a small Chinese restaurant run by a single family, Fiesta Mexican Restaurant, or Gary's, a small burger chain. There used to be a pizzeria, however it closed down a short time ago. There is a very small family-owned pharmacy called Maxwell and Halford Drug; funnily enough, they're best known for the Cherry Coca-Cola they sell. There is a small, but expensive grocery store called Independent Grocers Alliance, more commonly known as IGA. While it is the only grocery store in the entire town, many individuals only stop to pick up one or two items; most prefer to travel to a Walmart in Batesburg-Leesville in order to purchase the majority of their groceries. The most popular store in the entire town is Dollar General; this store sells a vast array of everyday items and it often busy from the moment it opens until closing time! There is a very small furniture store, Possibilities Furniture & More, run by a kind woman who is well-known within the community. The store has been in Johnston for a plethora of years and even employs two movers who will deliver the purchased furniture! Attached to the furniture store building is a small pet groomers called Clark's Cuts and Kennels. They provide a multitude of services such as daycare, boarding, grooming, nail grinding, bathing, etc. Both a doctor's and veterinary practice are situated away from the primary part of town; they are both very small practices, though well-equipped to aid the residents of Johnston. There is a single elementary school called Johnston Elementary School. Once students have completed fifth grade, they must attend both middle and high school in the next town over. There are technically no parks within the town, however they are currently in the midst of creating a 2.5 acre recreational area in order to provide families with more opportunities to enjoy outings and attract more visitors/potential residents. Admittedly there isn't much to do; there are no movie theaters, bowling alleys, "hang out" spots, playgrounds for children, areas to walk pets, or a large variety of restaurants. Despite this it's a nice town, so small that you could pass in the blink of an eye without realizing!
The first time I'd heard of my place, I was listening to a podcast about people who'd gone missing. It was a little surprising. Almost every apartment in the area was going for over a thousand dollars a month. I'd never heard anything about that story and neither had any of my friends. Maybe it's the struggle. I know a few of my friends cry themselves to sleep at night. Things are expensive, but we've learned how to be frugal over the years. You start to like the dusty smell of flea market toys and mothballed clothes. You smell a lot less in adulthood. You might start to smoke, or you might just be too accustomed to the state of things. But the flea market always asserts itself. The smell of adulthood is dusty magazines stacked on a closed piano. It wedges itself in the leather and stays in even after you wash it. Here, there're 3 thrift stores in walking distance. If you start on the far side, you can patronize two charity thrifts, a library, a rare book store, and a curio shop. Downtown is dense, cars and people fill the streets every morning, but you'd never hear it in the thrifts. No matter how many people or cars pass by, the store is silent. It's a nice place to lose an afternoon. Every year, there's more and more of those. Cars and people flood it. It's a developing city, they say. Headquartering one of the largest online empires for e-commerce and delivery, it's still showing growing pains. It reminds me of New York. Everything and everyone is set on their own goals, and there isn't a whole lot anyone asks from you. You can be alone, quiet, and independent, and people will leave you alone. It's not like the South, where being a little concerned means you care. You don't pry into anyone's life here, really. You can keep up your shell as long as you'd like, and the city will crash and roll back like waves on the beach. It's a lively place to be. Between the pianist next door and the two amateur vocalists upstairs, there's always something going on. In a way, we have less of an apartment of strangers and more a community of friends. We come together for our needs, celebrate birthdays, mourn funerals, and help each other when we can. In a way, I'm lucky to be here. I quite like most of my neighbors and they treat me pretty well. I try to make sure to clean after myself and leave them food and they do the same in kind. I bring mail to them and they to me. It's nice to see them and I believe they enjoy my presence as much as I do theirs. I live in a massive, dehumanizing modernist sprawl but it's people like my neighbors that make me feel like I didn't totally ruin my life.
The general area in which I live in can be described as your typical cookie cutter suburbia. For my neighborhood in particular, the presence of a homeowner's association is very apparent. Upon entering, you'll see nothing but well-maintained single family homes, which we can thank the homeowner's association for. The front yards are all very similar. There's a small patch of landscaped grass, some decorative pebbles, and rather short driveways. Every so often you'll see small trees as well. Everyone has a two car garage. As you continue to drive along throughout the neighborhood you'll see newly paved concrete. Despite many different families living here, the roads are in excellent condition. You won't find any potholes or anything like that here. Most of the houses are single story, but sometimes you'll see two stories as well. We don't have a typical mailbox set-up that you would expect for single family homes. There are no individual mailboxes in front of each house. Instead, it's more like apartments where there are a large grouping of mailboxes at the end of the street. Everyone uses a key to gain access their specific mailbox. And there's two larger lockers for packages. Again, you can thank the HOA and their obsession with uniformity for this. The location of my house is on the extreme edge of the nearby city, so my neighborhood can be described as part rural, part suburbs. As a result, we have a lot of land for, well, everything. There's multiple community pools to which anyone living here can access. It's well maintained and gated. And then there are various walking trails where you can walk your dog, or just go for an evening stroll by yourself. You don't have to visit a park to get your exercise in. The neighborhood is large enough that you can simply run around it and get more than enough exercise. Most of the community is made up of retired people. It's a very safe area, and everyone looks out for one another. Mixed in with that, we have a small amount of middle aged and young professionals too. In regards to the city, it's surprisingly large - at least by population - but also has a small time town feel. We have the vast majority of amenities that you come to expect and rely on. For example, we have a exactly one mall. It's not huge, but it gets the job done. For me, it takes around 15 minutes of driving to get anywhere significant, but once I do that, I am greeted with many different stores to choose from. We have everything from high end grocery stores where you can get organic food, to bargain outlets that only stock a small selection of items and has bare minimum staff to keep costs down. All in all, my neighborhood is safe, well-maintained, and pretty typical. We have a lot of nice things, like pools and walking trails. And although we aren't right next door to any sort of shopping, you can just hop in a car and go to any major chain that you'd like.
I live in a small Midwestern town that is just outside the suburban areas of a major city. My immediate neighborhood, on the east side of the town, could be described as the most economically disadvantaged area of the town. Property values are low, with most houses being rented to or owned by low-income individuals. However, it is not unattractive or unpleasant. My neighbors are generally friendly people who will smile and say hello when I walk down the street. Crime rates, while slightly higher than other parts of town, are still generally low. There have been a few violent crimes in the past ten years within a few blocks of my home, including a few shootings and at least one homicide. Our next door neighbors lost their son in a shooting outside an area bar last year. Fortunately, our family has not been directly affected by crime other than having an occasional item disappear from our porch if we forget to bring it inside. In general, the town in which I live has been profoundly affected by the “opioid epidemic” that has affected many parts of the United States. Many lives have been lost due to fentanyl overdoses. Fortunately, there are many resources in my town to combat this epidemic, including several addiction rehabilitation centers and Narcan training sessions for families and friends of those affected by addiction. Despite these challenges, this town has many positive attributes. My son’s elementary school has excellent staff, from the principal to the teachers and support staff. Despite having special needs, he has not faced any bullying thus far due to the incredibly positive atmosphere of the school, and he loves it there. We have an active PTO that plans multiple events throughout the year to promote family involvement and educational progress. Because over 20% of our town’s population lives below the poverty level, the elementary school provides free breakfast and lunch to all students, so that no child ever has to go hungry. No child or family is treated as “less than” due to an inability to pay, and costs for school fees, supplies, and field trips are very reasonable. The City Council and staff have made many improvements to the appearance of our town, including repaving roads, landscaping, and refurbishing city parks. Unfortunately, most of these improvements have taken place in the center of town and on the west side, where all of the shopping areas are located and most of the traffic passes through. The east side where I live tends to be neglected, which is a point of contention for those in my neighborhood. Overall, I do enjoy living in this town. People are generally friendly, the schools are great, there are enough shopping options (both small businesses and larger retail stores) to meet my family’s needs, and our home may not be worth much, but it is comfortable and adequate. Our family has lived here for over 16 years, and we cannot imagine living anywhere else.
My neighborhood is full of culture. It's set upon a hill, surrounded by buildings with historical meaning. I live in a 7 story apartment building right across from the old live Theater, and a block down The Hill, is this cool little arcade bar that different types of people flock to on warm summer nights. Often times, especially on the weekends in June and July, you will see a line of people waiting to get in. A few blocks up is the nearest city park. It's pretty big considering the part of town it sits in. Encircling the park is concrete, with tall stairs poured into the wall. During the frigid winter months, homeless people set their tents up in neat little rows along the sidewalk and along the wide steps. It doesn't snow much, but it rains, and the torrential down pour in the mid-winter months often tends to make it difficult to keep warm. Setting their tents up close together, in the center of town rather than out in the jungle, keeps them much warmer. They're also within reasonable walking and transit distance to the only family center for miles, where they can bathe and shower. What I love about my city though, isn't the beauty of the historic nature- the tall proud buildings, the architecture that is spattered through-out the varying levels of the hills that roll down towards the ocean. What I love about my neighborhood is the culture of the people themselves. You see, Hilltop once was the most notorious neighborhood on the West Coast for gang violence. You still hear stories, even three decades later, about the federal government officials and the DEA sweeping through like a broom, trying to clean the streets. The people, they don't forget. Stories are still passed from generation to generation, on through to transplants like me, of those days. The people work hard, even though it's still considered one of the rougher 'hoods' in the entire city, to keep it cleaned up. They still care about what goes on in their city, on their block. They say that if you're white, you shouldn't walk around the Hill after dark. Truly, I believe that this warning is reminiscent of the old days, and it is tinged with the sour taste of social conditioning. Perhaps it is that I am just dark enough to pass for a not entirely "white-girl," or maybe Hilltop recognizes me as one of their own, someone who is just as painfully aware of the reminders that constantly plague our nation. Reminders that racism, cultural conditioning, and assumptions are made out of ignorance and fear, even in a city that is supposed to be a cultural melting pot Utopia. I know one thing: no matter how far I roam, the Hilltop is home. I feel alive walking those streets at night, meeting people who have more quickly and rarely nefariously offered me a jacket than to rob me. It's a place where laundromat owners have stayed open just a few minutes later so I could charge my phone when I had no where to escape from the rain. It's a place where I have sat, believe myself to be invisible, huddled against concrete store fronts on the most grey dreary of nights, only to have someone stop and look me in the eye, hand me a $5, and tell me I'm beautiful and valuable.
I live in Rural America, specifically small town Michigan. Where you go from farmland to small tourist cities. There is no big city malls, no Wal-mart, Target, or even an Applebee’s. Anywhere you need to go, you have to drive to get to. Despite that I live in one of the most beautiful places in the world surrounded by water. My “city” is surrounded by water. Beautiful Lake Michigan to one side, and Lake Charlevoix on the other. Everywhere you go you can find a beach to dip your toes in. My neighborhood, reflects the idea of small town. Houses are not stacked upon one another. They aren’t cookie cutter houses that are built the same. They are older homes, some of them being updated and remodeled some of them being older. Most homes have basements. Full Basements that you can see from the road. Many houses in the neighborhood have older aluminum siding. We have houses every color you can imagine in the blocks that surround my house. Most of the houses have yards. Yards with trampolines, and playsets. Some people have gardens, and fences for their animals. The houses resemble Middle America. Hard working people who work to make a living and are either raising families or have raised families. On any given day you will see kids running up and down the streets. You will also see people walking dogs, biking and rollerblading. Neighbors know neighbors and you can recognize who fits in and who doesn’t belong. You will see someone grilling outside and wave, or even someone that is walking their dog from a few blocks down and smile pleasantly. The lawns are kept in decent condition. Nobody has leaves piled up from fall time. Green grass is kept mowed and under control. If people have plants and bushes in their yards they are kept trimmed down. It isn’t a beautiful neighborhood that you drive into and think wow look at the nice homes, but one you drive into and think you can tell this would be a good place to raise a family. It’s quiet, peaceful and, and safe. While only average looking, it is exceptional for the fact that it represents what people want in the world, which is a safe place to land at the end of the day. Within walking distance there is the county sheriff’s department and jail. The Health department is just next to that. The city recycling center sits just down the road, and neighbors and residents from around the city utilize the services they provide. We have baseball and softball fields nearby where you can hear the announcers keeping score and calling the names of players. Our small town airport is next to that. You can be playing outside, or even inside and hear the rumbles of small engine planes taking off and landing. You can walk to get ice cream from the local ice cream place, and if you are really into it you can make it downtown from our neighborhood of homes. My kids can ride their bikes to the park which is only 8 blocks or so away. It is a really great place to live.
transformed_texts:
I live in a big city. My neighborhood is very different. People from many countries live here. Residential areas and businesses are not together in one place. Some areas are homes and some are stores, restaurants, and places to have fun. There are many new restaurants and stores to visit. Some stores are well-known, big companies. Other stores are small and popular. These stores are in malls and on the streets. The streets are close to quiet neighborhoods.

There are parks near my home. People take their children to these parks. My neighborhood is also home to many different kinds of people. There is a community for people who are LGBTQ+, an Orthodox Jewish community, and people from the Soviet Union. Outside my neighborhood, there are more people from different countries. However, they are often in their own groups. We have Korea town, China town, Little Armenia, and more. These areas are not very far from my neighborhood.

But it takes a long time to drive between these areas. We have a lot of traffic. People do not usually walk in my city. Even if places are close, it is hard to walk because the city is big. We have a lot of problems with traffic and parking. There are also many new buildings being built. Some people like this, but others are unhappy. They are worried about more people coming to the city.

There are many kinds of homes in my city. Not everyone lives in a big apartment building. We have single-family homes, smaller apartment buildings, and condominiums. Even in my neighborhood, there are different kinds of homes. People of all ages live here. I do not know most of my neighbors. It is not like it used to be when I was a kid. I used to play with my neighbors and friends.

My neighborhood is interesting. Most houses are for one family. But some homes are divided into two, still connected. My house has a small yard in front and a small driveway to the side. It looks like the past when people wanted to live in the suburbs. This was the American dream. People thought it was perfect. But now it's changing. My neighborhood still looks the same. It still seems like the American dream is real. The people here are holding on to it. They still have cars in their driveways. Kids still play outside. The public school has been here for almost 90 years. It still looks to the future. It makes the young people happy. It makes old people remember the past. There are not many churches. But the basketball courts are full. The houses look different. But they feel the same. There is a big store called Super A. It is owned by a family of Yemenis. They are one of the few Arab families here. Most people are African American. The streets are wide. The kids play football. They stop when cars come. Most people have lived here for a long time. They know each other. There was a karate school. But when the kids stopped wanting to be karate fighters, it became a pharmacy. There is a small movie theater. It shows old movies at a low price. The kids don't like it. But the old people like it. There is a highway that goes through our town. But the entrance and exit are in the next town. We once wanted a special exit. The young people wanted it. But the old people said no. They thought the highway would ruin our town. We are building a new school. We are choosing a symbol for our town. I think a cyborg with a country accent and a cabin would be the best symbol.

You might not notice it at first. This is a residential area behind a shopping strip. It does not look like a place where people live. But if you go behind the old, empty store, you will see a busy community. Behind the hotels, you can find many apartments lined up in a row. These apartments are near a community college. The college has a small campus with quiet buildings. Students go there to learn and sleep in. They come in through iron gates one by one. People who drive to work are stuck in traffic because of the students. The road meets another road with a park on one side. There is a center to help people who are hurt. The center has nice furniture on the porch and a fan that moves the air. Children play in the park across the street. They run and play while bees fly around the flowers. Old people walk their dogs and watch the teenagers on skateboards. There is a place to eat sushi near the park. It is not very busy. There is also a store to buy things for swimming pools and a place to get a nail job. You can buy food and get a manicure at the same time. There is a place that sells frozen yogurt, too. Teenagers eat frozen yogurt while they do tricks on their skateboards. This neighborhood is like a piece of American history. It is a quiet place where not much changes.

She asked, "Where are we?" as we drove past many fields of corn that went on forever. I said, "This is it!" knowing she would be surprised by the open space. She came from a town where the grocery store was near her house. She had never seen so much open space before. I told her what it was like to grow up in a small town in Ohio. In that moment, she understood who I was and where I came from.

We drove down a small country road. There was a big hole in the ground with water in it. Just past it was where I live. The houses are made of brick and stucco. Each house has a big piece of land around it that people take care of. In the spring, there are many flowers and trees that change color with the seasons. The driveways are full of nice cars. The people who live here are very happy and take care of their homes.

As we walked down the road, I saw my Korean neighbor. He was outside and friendly. He uses a big machine to cut the grass and likes to sing while he works. Everyone in the neighborhood likes him. He has a special story. He used to be a doctor, but now he is older and a little slower. He is still a kind person.

We finally arrived at my house. There are many geese in the yard. Our dog chases them. There is a small stream that goes into the big hole in the ground. I can hear frogs, the stream, and sometimes a cow from a nearby farm. Across a small bridge made of wood, there is a special place with many trees, herbs, and flowers that grow naturally. This is where I spent most of my childhood. I built forts and played with my friends. We had a lot of fun.

In the winter, it can be very cold. But it's also very beautiful. The trees are bare and the yard is empty. If it snows, a beautiful winter wonderland appears. My sister and I would make snow angels and build snowmen. We would also make forts out of branches. We would play pretend and use our imaginations. We were happy kids who didn't have to worry about anything.

Portland, Oregon is a city that likes to be different. The city's unofficial slogan is "Keep Portland Weird." To some people, this is a reminder of the city's past. It was a time when Portland was not as well-known and not as expensive. Many creative and unique cultures developed here. To others, "Keep Portland Weird" is a message saying, "Come to Portland, where you can be different and be accepted for it."

Even with many new people moving to Portland and new buildings going up, the city is still strange. Strange does not mean we do not have modern things. We buy many things from other countries. But strange means we can accept things that others do not. Portland has many normal things too, like yoga and business people.

In my neighborhood, the streets have colorful houses, gardens with flowers and vegetables, and free boxes. Free boxes are boxes with things people are giving away. You might find clothes, books, or something else. It is like treasure hunting. This is a big part of what Portland is about, but it is just my way of being weird. People around me might not want to get things from free boxes. They might go to a special yoga class with goats or a soccer game.

Portland has many people who love many things. Some people like to drink and some people like to pursue their dreams. But Portland also has problems. Some people use too many drugs and struggle with their mental health. The rain and gray skies all year might make them feel worse. Portland also has a homelessness problem. We have good services for the homeless, but they are not enough. The people who do not live on the streets have mixed feelings about this problem. They are not weird about this.

The mountains are always there. They are in the north. They see the sun every morning and every evening. They do not care about my work or my life. They are always there, strong and steady. 

When I am very stressed, I look at the mountains. They calm my worried heart. They help me feel strong enough to go on. I first saw these mountains when I started college. They are near the campus. The university has many beautiful things. But the mountains are the most beautiful thing to me.

The rest of the town is also nice. There are many cafés where I study. I can walk or take a bus to the downtown area. It is old and very interesting. But the mountains are the best part. This town has two different feelings. It is like a big city, but also quiet and peaceful. I can walk to the library and be in a quiet place. I can also walk to the busy downtown area. This makes this town very exciting.

I have many happy memories of this town. I walk with my friends in the park after a long night studying. I also walk to the downtown area to see a movie. But this town also has sad memories. I sit by the pond and think about life. I see the turtles and ducks living their lives. I wonder what my purpose is. So I walk to the main street. The sun shines and I look up. I see the mountains. They are strong and beautiful. They remind me to keep going.

If you plan to visit Bensonhurt, Brooklyn, you will not have trouble finding it. Public transportation is easy to use. Many people in New York City use it. Bensonhurt is a busy neighborhood, so you will still feel like you are in New York City. You will see many Asian stores when you visit. Many Asian people live in Bensonhurt. This is why you will see an Asian store on almost every block. These stores are very popular. They are good places to buy food, wash clothes, and other things. Many local people like these stores because the food is good, the prices are low, and it is convenient. There are many of these stores near where I live. You can walk to four stores within a few minutes. This makes it easy to buy grocery.

Bensonhurt is not only Asian people. It is also home to many immigrants and their families. Many big businesses in the area are owned by Asian people. There is also a park near where I live. It is a good place to play sports or relax. The park has many things, including basketball courts, a big field, and a playground for kids.

The neighborhood is not very tall. You will not see many big buildings. Most of the houses are two-family homes. The people who live here are usually nice. However, it can be noisy. You may hear loud music from cars or people speeding by. If you visit at night, be careful. Some people can be mean and cause trouble. I was bullied in this neighborhood a long time ago, but I am safe now. There are also people who steal packages. Some people do not clean up after their dogs. You will see dog waste on the ground as you walk to the train or store. My biggest problem is dog waste on the floor everywhere I go.

I live in a place without many sidewalks. Everything flows downhill, and my house is at the top of a very steep hill. People call it the "work out hill" because runners like to run up it. There are no sidewalks on my street, so people walk on the road. The road has holes in it, and it can be hard to drive on.

During storms, branches and other things often fall on the power lines. The lines need repair, so they look badly fixed. There are many tall evergreen trees around. But people here do not like the trees. They want to cut down as many as they can because the trees block the view of the ocean. Many houses are built high up on the hill to see the ocean. They have big windows to see the water. It is beautiful at sunset when the water shines and the sky turns orange.

But it is often cloudy and damp. Moss grows on everything. I once left my car in my driveway for a month. When I came back, it was covered in moss. It took me three hours to clean it off. Most people who live here are older, like retired people. There are not many children around. Instead, many people have dogs. They run around in the street, and if you leave a door or window open, they might get in. I once found a dog in my living room and had to chase it out.

There are also many wild rabbits. They dig up plants and make holes in people's lawns. My cats like to hunt them. We also see birds like small sparrows and hummingbirds. Sometimes a hawk or eagle comes by, but the crows chase it away.

There are no stores near my house, but if you walk down the hill to the waterfront, there are some restaurants that serve fresh seafood. There is no wide beach, but it is fun to throw rocks into the water. The bay is not very wide, so you can see the other side even on cloudy days.

I live in a quiet neighborhood in a small town in Tennessee. It is near two state highways, so we have some traffic. But mostly, it is quiet. Not many new people move here. I know most of my neighbors. They work in their yards and do their daily jobs. In the winter, my friends and I like to sled down a hill on our street. Our house is at the corner of the street, so we see people all day. We notice when a new car comes to the neighborhood. Some neighbors walk their dogs or exercise. Children ride their bikes. We work from home. There are four of us: my wife and our two daughters, 11 and 14 years old. We see our neighbors often. We like to play outside and sometimes even when it rains. We have a barbecue on our back deck. It smells good. We hear lawn mowers almost every day from March to October. Our neighborhood has many trees. It was a forest before. So, it is cool in the summer and there are many leaves in the fall. We have to rake and burn the leaves every year. I like the smell of burning leaves. Lately, it has not been cold enough to be winter. It just seems like fall is long. I like to work in my garage. It is at the back of our house. I like to fix my truck there. When I open the garage doors, I feel connected to the neighborhood. On holidays, it is quiet. Some neighbors visit their families from out of town. I like living here. If it were not a main street, it would be perfect.

My home is in the middle of the desert. There is a lot of dirt. It is hard to understand what it is like to live here unless you have lived here. The ground is usually brown. If someone has a green lawn, they must spend a lot of money to take care of it. When I first moved here, it was very quiet. Now, many new houses have been built. The area is becoming more and more like a city.

Most people are friendly here. But, like any city, there are good and bad parts. I live near many older people. They are friendly. The stores in our area are mostly big chains like Food for Less and Smart and Final. If you want to buy healthy food, you have to go somewhere else. 

The main jobs in our city are in construction. Many people work in this field. The city is still growing and there is a lot of empty space. I am a construction worker. I install drywall and T-bars. I like living here because of the animals. People come to the desert for its beauty. The desert has a hard environment that needs protection. It is home to many kinds of wildlife. It is good to learn about the animals that live here so we can live together safely.

My family and I have learned to accept the wildlife. My children like catching lizards and desert bugs. They are outside right now trying to catch them. We have some fun things to do here. If you come to Victorville, you can visit the San Bernardino County Fair. It is a fun event. If you like winter sports, you can go to Wrightwood and see the snow-covered mountains. If you are interested in the natural history and culture of the desert, you can visit the Victor Valley Museum. It has many interesting things to see.

When I think of my neighborhood, I think of my college campus. I live in a dormitory and consider the people who live there my community. I also think of the campus around me as my neighborhood, but to a lesser degree. My neighborhood is different from others because I am a student and live in a dorm. But it has some things in common with other neighborhoods.

My neighborhood has houses, people, stores, and parks. Let's talk about the houses. There are three kinds of houses near me. There are apartments, houses, and dorms. In the apartments, 2-4 people live in a room. There are 4-6 rooms on each floor. Each building has about 20 people. Some houses have 2-4 bedrooms and are for people who work at the school. There are not many of these. The most common kind of house is the dorm. It has two people in a room, and there are many of these.

My school values diversity, and this is true of my neighborhood. People from many cultures and ages live here. Some staff live in houses, and students live in dorms or apartments. The people in my neighborhood are a mix of young and old, from many countries. They are a lively and interesting group. Now, let's talk about the stores and parks. My school has many stores, including places to eat and buy food. There are also stores that sell school clothes and other things. Anything you need can be found in my neighborhood. The park is a fun place for everyone to play. It is clean and safe because of the people who live here.

I have lived in this neighborhood for about 10 years. When I first came, I was sad. I missed my old home in Riverdale. But my parents wanted the best for me and my sister. We moved to a new neighborhood in Stockbridge. It was a better place to live. I got used to it and made new friends. I also made some enemies at school. I did not know my neighbors very well. But I knew Mr. Glen and his children. They were nice people. I consider them like family. I went to Mr. Glen's wedding. It was fun. I hope to have a wedding like that someday.

The neighborhood is like a maze. But now I have a GPS. I can explore it. I have a friend named Kason. We play video games together. We also go to the park. I like to play with sticks and practice my balance. I also like to bring my wooden sword and practice sword fighting. There is a basketball court and a tennis court. I used to play tennis with my dad and my friend. We had fun. I hope to play again someday.

I have had many good times in this neighborhood. I have many stories. But these are the things that I remember. I think the best times are yet to come.

My home is close to the college where I study. I like living here. There are many apartment buildings, a few restaurants, and some bars. These places are fun to visit and not too expensive. One of the bars changed its name. It is more expensive now, but the service and drinks are not bad. Most of the people here are nice. They are students or have lower incomes. The apartment prices are low. There is an elementary school near my home. Many children live here.

I do not know my neighbors. They smoke a lot. The building management put a device to remove smells near their door. My boyfriend and I found it funny. It is almost like they are saying something bad about my neighbors. The buildings around me are old-looking, but maybe they have new inside. A little down the street, there are new apartments. I do not like them because the workers built them cheaply. The rent is high, but the building management can charge too much because it is close to the university.

I live near a restaurant that is very cheap. They serve food on paper plates. Most of their food comes from a microwave. Across from the restaurant is a gas station. I have heard it is not a good place to work. But the city fixed the road near my home last summer. Now there is a nice sidewalk, green grass, and the area looks better.

Behind my apartment building are many trees. The management cut some of them down, so there are some tree stumps. But there are more trees here than down the street. Behind my building is another line of trees and more apartments. I live on 42nd Street. The street behind mine, 43rd Street, is not as nice. The sidewalk is broken, and the buildings look old. There are many trees on this street, but maybe they hide how old the buildings look. Some apartments near me have a lot of problems and a lot of people come and go. I think I like my home. I can afford it, and there are many good things near me. I like that the university is within walking distance and there are two bus stops where I can go to the store or downtown easily.

My neighborhood is a group of houses that look like individual homes. They are not too close to each other. The houses are painted yellow with white porches and green metal roofs. Almost all of the people in the neighborhood are friends. We meet at the end of the street some evenings and talk. The children play with their toys, draw on the sidewalk or fly kites. It is nice to be here. The world is very busy with computers and machines. It feels like a simple time. We are surrounded by fields and trees with blue skies and white clouds. But sometimes we have bad weather. Recently, we had a warning about a tornado. We heard the warning sirens and went to a safe place. I was in my bathtub with my little dog. My big dog was in the living room, barking. The neighborhood was quiet except for loud hail hitting the ground. After the storm, the road was hot and steaming. It went from hot to cool in a short time. The hail melted when it hit the hot pavement. Then the sun came out and it started to rain. I saw a beautiful double rainbow. I took a picture with my camera. The neighborhood was quiet for a while after the storm. Then people came home and it was business as usual. Mothers and children were outside, cooking dinner. I like my neighborhood. I moved here from New Hampshire to North Carolina. I like the way people talk here. I have a two-bedroom apartment. So does everyone else. But the apartments are not the same inside. Some are small. I like to walk in the big field behind my house. I go to the pond that is not for swimming. I see deer and hear a big frog singing in the morning. It is a great place to live, just 40 minutes from the city of Charlotte. Each morning I hear roosters crowing from the farms around here. It is like living in a small village. We even have a donkey at a farm nearby that brays in the evening. I am lucky to live here.

I moved to this neighborhood in eighth grade. It was hard to make friends at first, but I got close to two guys who lived nearby. They are not living here anymore, but I still remember the good times. Most of the people who lived here when I moved in are still here. My neighborhood is like many American suburbs. The houses are two stories high and have yards. Children play outside on nice days. The neighborhood is usually quiet. I have never had a problem with the people here. You can be alone unless you need help. I have ordered many packages online, and they have always been safe on my porch. I trust my neighbors. There is a park near my house where I played basketball, football, and baseball with my friends. I also got hurt playing football, but that is not a bad memory. When I visit the park now, I see my cousin's kids playing on the swings and slides. They are happy when they think about going to the park. The park makes me happy too. My neighborhood is different. You can find many kinds of food nearby. There are Chinese, Indian, Mexican, and Italian restaurants within a short walk. Many people order food from apps like GrubHub and DoorDash. We also have fast food places and pizza shops. The stores have everything we need. There are dry cleaners, a Walgreens, a CVS, and a Jewel-Osco grocery store. We even have an Indian store where you can buy food to make at home. I like my neighborhood. When I see bad news about neighbors on social media, I am grateful for mine.

My home is in a small town in South Carolina. It is not very different from other towns in the area. But it is very important for growing food. Johnston is known as the World's Peach Capital. The town is proud of this title and shows it on signs. The town is mostly fields with many peach trees or cows. Houses are far apart and are two stories high. Some have metal roofs to keep them cool in the hot summer. Others have gray roofs. The houses are not usually near the road. They are farther back so people can use the front fields for animals or crops. In the middle of town, there is one traffic light. This is where the town's stores are. There are three places to get fast food: Hong Kong, a small Chinese restaurant; Fiesta Mexican Restaurant; and Gary's, a small burger place. There used to be a pizza place, but it closed. There is a small pharmacy called Maxwell and Halford Drug. They are famous for selling Cherry Coca-Cola. There is a small grocery store called IGA. People often go to a bigger store in another town to buy most of their groceries. The most popular store is Dollar General. People buy many things there every day. There is a small furniture store run by a kind woman. She has been in business for a long time. There is also a pet groomer next door. They take care of dogs and give them a bath. There are small doctor's and veterinarian offices in the town. The schools in the town are small. Students go to a bigger school in the next town after fifth grade. The town is making a park to give people a place to go and have fun. It will be a nice place to visit and live.

The first time I heard about my place, I was listening to a podcast about people who were missing. It was a surprise. Many apartments in the area cost over one thousand dollars a month. I had never heard of this story before, and neither had my friends. 

Life is expensive, but we have learned to be careful with money. We like to visit flea markets and buy old things. They smell good. Adult life can be boring, but flea markets are not. They are always interesting.

There are three second-hand shops near my home. If I start at one end, I can visit two shops that help poor people, a library, a store with old books, and a store with strange things. The streets are crowded, but it is quiet inside the shops. People and cars go by, but I do not hear them.

I like to visit these shops. They are good places to spend an afternoon. Every year, more people come to live here. It is a growing city. A big company that sells things online has its headquarters here. But the city still has problems. It reminds me of New York. People here are busy with their own lives. They do not ask many questions. I can be alone and quiet, and people will leave me alone.

It is not like the South, where people care about each other. Here, people are independent. They do not ask personal questions. I can keep to myself if I want. The city is a lively place to live. There are musicians and singers who play music near my home. It is nice to live in a place where I have friends. We help each other. We celebrate birthdays and funerals together. We try to take care of each other.

I am lucky to live here. My neighbors are nice. I try to be clean and share food with them. They do the same for me. We take care of each other's mail. It is nice to see them and be around them.

I live in a big, modern city. But my neighbors make me feel happy. They are good people.

I live in a common kind of neighborhood called suburbia. My neighborhood is part of a bigger community with rules, called a homeowner's association. The rules keep the neighborhood clean and nice. When you enter the neighborhood, you see many homes that are similar. They are all single-family homes with grass, small trees, and short driveways. The roads are in good condition and are not broken. Most homes are one story, but some are two stories. There are no separate boxes for mail in front of each house. Instead, there is a big group of boxes at the end of the street. You need a key to open your box. The neighborhood is on the edge of a city, so it has a lot of space. We have big pools and walking paths where you can take your dog or walk alone. The neighborhood is safe and people help each other. Many people who live here are older, but we also have some middle-aged and young people. The city near my neighborhood is big, but it feels small. We have many things you need, like a mall. I can drive to the mall in about 15 minutes and find many stores. I can buy healthy food at one store or cheap things at another store. My neighborhood is safe and nice. We have many good things, like pools and walking paths. It takes a little time to get to big stores, but I can drive there easily.

I live in a small town in the Midwest. My town is near a big city, but it is not in the city area. My neighborhood is on the east side of the town. It is one of the poorer areas. Homes here are not very expensive, and many people rent or own them. But my neighborhood is not bad or ugly. Most people in my neighborhood are friendly. They say hello when I walk by. There are some problems with crime here. There have been a few violent crimes in the past ten years. But they are not very common. We have had some problems with things going missing from our porch. Our family has not been directly hurt by crime.

Our town has a big problem with the opioid epidemic. Many people in the United States have this problem. Our town is one of them. Many people have died from overdoses. We have some good resources to help people with this problem. There are places where people can go for help. We also have training to help people who know someone with addiction.

But our town also has good things. My son's elementary school is very good. The teachers and staff are kind. My son is in school there, and he likes it. He has special needs, but he has not been bullied. The school is a happy place. The school provides food for all students. No one has to go hungry. The school also does not charge a lot for things like school supplies and field trips.

Our town's government is trying to make the town better. They have fixed some roads and parks. But most of this work has been done in the center of town and on the west side, where people shop and drive. My neighborhood on the east side is not as lucky. This is a problem for us.

I like living in our town. People are friendly, the schools are good, and we have enough stores to buy what we need. Our home is not expensive, but it is comfortable. We have lived here for 16 years. We do not want to live anywhere else.

My neighborhood is full of culture. It is on a hill. The buildings here are old and have a lot of history. I live in a 7-story apartment building near an old theater. Across the street from my building is a small bar. People from many different groups come to this bar on warm summer nights. On weekends in June and July, you see a long line of people waiting to get in. Near my home is a big park. It is not very big, but it is nice. The park is surrounded by concrete. There are many stairs in the walls. During cold winter months, homeless people set up their tents in a row on the sidewalk and on the stairs. It does not snow much here, but it rains. The rain can make it hard to stay warm. The homeless people like to stay close together. This keeps them warmer. They are close to a place where they can get food, clothes, and take a bath.

I like my city. I like the people. They work hard to make their neighborhood clean. They still care about what happens in their city. People tell stories about the past. Thirty years ago, this neighborhood was known for violence. The government came to clean up the streets. The people remember. They tell the stories to their children and to new people who move here. They say to be careful if you are white and walk around here at night. I think this is because of old stories. Some people think this is true, but I do not. I think it is because of fear and not knowing the truth. I am a little dark-skinned, so people may think I am one of them. I know that I am safe here. People are kind and helpful. They give me things when I need them. They say I am beautiful and valuable. I love walking around here at night. I feel alive. The people here are my family.

I live in Rural America. My home is in a small town in Michigan. It is a beautiful place. There is no big city here. If I need to go somewhere, I have to drive. But I like it because I live near two big lakes. One is Lake Michigan. The other is Lake Charlevoix. I can easily find a beach to visit. My neighborhood is a small town. Houses are not stacked on top of each other. They are old and different from one another. Some people update their houses or fix them up. Most houses have basements. You can see them from the street. Many houses have aluminum siding. The houses are different colors. People have yards with trampolines, playsets, and gardens. Some people have fences for their animals. The houses look like the kind of homes in a place called Middle America. People work hard to make a living. Some people are raising families. On any day, you will see kids playing outside and people walking dogs or biking. Neighbors know each other. If you see someone you know, you will wave or smile. The lawns are well kept. People do not leave leaves on the ground. The grass is cut and the plants are trimmed. Our neighborhood is quiet and peaceful. It is a safe place to live. It is not a beautiful neighborhood, but it is a good place to live. It is a place people would like to raise a family. There is a police station and a jail near my house. There is also a place where people can recycle and a health department. We have baseball and softball fields. You can hear the announcers calling the game. There is a small airport nearby. You can hear the planes flying in and out. We have an ice cream shop and a park. My kids can ride their bikes to the park. It is a great place to live.
